check_poldek is nagios plugin for monitoring systems using poldek as package
manager (PLD Linux, or any rpm-based system using poldek). It checks if new
system updates are available.

commandline options:

  -v          - be verbose (prints errors on stderr)
  -c N        - report error if there are >= N packages to install
  -w N        - report warning if there are >= N packages to install
  --cache DIR - use DIR as poldek cache (default: /tmp/check_poldek)

example configuration:

  nrpe.cfg:
    command[check_poldek]=/usr/lib/nagios/plugins/check_poldek --cache /var/cache/check_poldek -c 10 -w 5
  
  services.cfg:
    define service {
            use                             generic-service
            host_name                       example_pld_machine
            service_description             POLDEK
            check_command                   check_remote_timeout!check_poldek!60
    }

